## 3. Inputs and Outputs

**Inputs:** {{#if hasInputs}}prompts and user-provided context from {{config.siteName}} features documented in the AI Usage Policy{{else}}minimal prompts triggered by specific user actions{{/if}}. We do not send passwords, payment information, government IDs, health records, or data about third parties.

**Outputs:** text (and where applicable, images) returned to the user in the feature's UI. Outputs carry an AI-generated label where shown.

---

## 4. Performance and Accuracy

Accuracy claims of the underlying model are owned by {{system.provider}} and documented in their model card / system card. We rely on those claims and apply the following deployer-side checks:

- **Output validation:** responses are not executed as code; text outputs are rendered as text only.
- **Rate limiting:** requests are rate-limited per user to bound the blast radius of malformed or malicious inputs.
- **Manual spot-checks:** outputs are reviewed periodically as part of site maintenance.

Quantitative benchmarks against our specific use case have not been established; we do not claim specific accuracy percentages for our integration.

---

## 5. Human Oversight (EU AI Act Article 14)

- **Before deployment:** the integration is reviewed via pull request under our repository's branch-protection rules (required reviewer count surfaced by the scanner).
- **At runtime:** {{config.ownerName}} has the ability to immediately disable the feature via a deployment push that removes the call site or an environment-variable kill switch.
- **After output:** any user can request human review of a specific AI-produced output by contacting [{{config.contactEmail}}](mailto:{{config.contactEmail}}).

---

## 6. Risk Management (EU AI Act Article 9)

Known risks of deploying {{system.provider}} at {{config.siteName}}:

- **Hallucination** — the model can produce confident-but-wrong output. Mitigation: outputs are labelled as AI-generated; users are advised to verify safety-critical information independently.
- **Injection** — user input could attempt to steer the model against its instructions. Mitigation: system prompts are server-side, not user-editable; outputs are not passed to downstream tools without validation.
- **Data leakage** — sending user input to a third-party model provider is itself a data flow. Mitigation: documented in the AI Usage Policy; we do not opt in to provider training data collection where an opt-out is offered.
- **Availability** — provider outages disable the AI feature but do not disable the rest of the site.
{{#if system.isProhibitedRisk}}
- **Misuse for prohibited practices** — the risk tier was heuristically classified as prohibited. Action required: review use and either refactor the feature or declare the correct risk_tier under ai_systems in .grc/config.yml.
{{/if}}

---

## 7. Data Governance (EU AI Act Article 10)

This model card describes a *deployer* integration; training data is held by {{system.provider}}. For our inputs:

- **Source:** directly from users, in real time, only when they use an AI-powered feature.
- **Lawful basis:** consent — by using the feature, the user consents to the input being sent to {{system.provider}} for processing.
- **Bias checks:** no systematic bias testing has been performed at the integration layer; we rely on the provider's own fairness evaluations.

---

## 8. Logging and Record Keeping (EU AI Act Article 12)

Request logs for this integration include: timestamp, request hash, provider, latency, success / failure. Input and output content are **not** logged by default to minimize data retention. Logs are retained for {{config.logRetentionDays}} days.

